            "en_html": "<p>A decade ago the Hagglunds factory, owned by BAE Systems, Britain’s biggest defence firm, was cutting costs to survive. Today it is expanding its capacity five- or six-fold to fulfil soaring orders. Revenue has surged from $211m in 2018 to $1.1bn in 2025, and is heading “north of $2bn” a year, says Tommy Gustafsson-Rask, the general manager. The workforce has more than tripled since 2021, to around 2,600.</p>",
            "zh_text": "十年前，英国最大防务企业BAE系统公司旗下的赫格隆工厂为求生存而压缩成本。如今，该厂正将产能扩大五至六倍，以完成激增的订单。总经理汤米·古斯塔夫松-拉斯克表示，营收已从2018年的2.11亿美元飙升至2025年的11亿美元，并有望「突破每年20亿美元」。员工人数自2021年以来增长了两倍多，达到约2,600人。"
