            "en_html": "<p>WOMEN HAVE made extraordinary gains in the past few decades across the rich world. They now outnumber men on university campuses in virtually every wealthy country. At work, many have been enthusiastically “leaning in”, as Sheryl Sandberg, then Facebook’s second-in-command, urged them to do in a book in 2013. Their representation among the highest-paying professions, including medicine and the law, has nearly tripled in America since 1980. At the turn of the century a British patient was twice as likely to see a man. Last year the number of female physicians exceeded those of men for the first time, according to Britain’s General Medical Council, a public body.</p>",
            "zh_text": "过去几十年间,女性在富裕世界取得了非凡的进步。如今在几乎每一个富裕国家,她们在大学校园里的数量都超过了男性。在职场上,许多人正热忱地\"向前一步\"——这正是雪莉·桑德伯格(时任Facebook二号人物)2013年在书中发出的号召。自1980年以来,在美国薪酬最高的职业(包括医学和法律)中,女性占比几乎增至三倍。本世纪初,英国患者见到男医生的几率是见到女医生的两倍。而据英国公共机构——医学总会的数据,去年女医生的数量首次超过了男医生。"
