            "en_html": "<p>Recently, however, the most highly qualified cohort of women in human history has often appeared to be leaning out. In 2024 a study by S&amp;P Global, a compiler of indices, found that women’s share of executive positions in listed American companies fell for the first time in 2023 after nearly 20 years of uninterrupted growth. In 2025 women secured 38% of new board seats at companies in the S&amp;P 500 index of large American firms, down from 42% the previous year and prolonging a retreat from their peak in 2020.</p>",
            "zh_text": "然而近来,人类历史上学历最高的这批女性,却似乎正在\"向后靠\"。指数编制公司标普全球2024年的一项研究发现,在美国上市公司的执行岗位中,女性占比在连续近20年增长后,于2023年首次出现下滑。2025年,在标普500指数成分股公司的新增董事会席位中,女性获得的比例为38%,低于前一年的42%,延续了自2020年峰值以来的回落之势。"
