            "en_html": "<p>Drive around Silicon Valley and you will see surprisingly little skyline. The landscape is dotted with low-rise offices, bungalows and malls. The microchips that gave the region its name are built in much the same way. Millions of low-rise transistors—the electrical switches which instantiate a binary 1 or 0, and thus form the basis of computing—are plonked next to each other on a wafer of silicon.</p>",
            "zh_text": "驾车穿越硅谷,你会惊讶地发现这里几乎看不到高楼林立的天际线。点缀其间的是低矮的办公楼、平房和购物中心。赋予这一地区以名字的微芯片,其制造方式也大抵如此。数以百万计的低矮晶体管——那些将二进制1或0实例化、从而构成计算基础的电子开关——被随意地彼此紧挨着摆放在一块硅晶圆上。"
